# Future Readiness Index (FRI) Portal - Project Requirements Document

## Project Overview

The Future Readiness Index (FRI) Portal is a comprehensive platform developed for SBF (Singapore Business Federation) to help companies assess their future readiness, benchmark against industry peers, and receive actionable recommendations.

## Core Modules & Requirements

### 1. Landing Page

**Purpose**: Introductory information and credibility signals

- FRI Initiative Overview
- Login/Registration functionality
- Benefits explanation
- Trusted By logos display
- Testimonials/Case Studies showcase

### 2. Dashboard

**Purpose**: Central hub for company users after login

- FRI Score Display with visual indicators
- Survey Progress Tracker with completion status
- Direct link to Report Viewer
- Notification system for updates
- Delegation Overview Widget for team management
- Benchmarking Preview & Overview

### 3. Survey System

**Purpose**: Collects assessment data from organisations

- Dynamic Survey Engine with adaptive questioning
- Dimension-based sections for structured assessment
- Sector-specific logic for targeted questions
- Auto-Save & Resume functionality
- Tooltips/Instructions for user guidance
- ACRA Auto-fill with manual override capability
- Skip Financial Questions option for sensitive data

### 4. Report Viewer

**Purpose**: Visualises results and recommendations

- Interactive Charts (radar, bar, trend visualizations)
- Online + PDF report generation
- Personalised recommendations engine
- Heatmap display (strengths & gaps analysis)
- Benchmarking (sector, regional, global comparisons)
- Integration links to Knowledge Hub

### 5. Knowledge Centre

**Purpose**: Resource repository for learning materials

- Filter/Search by sector, dimension, keyword
- CMS management capabilities (Admin controlled)
- Toolkits, templates, case studies, and multimedia content

### 6. Support Page

**Purpose**: User assistance and help resources

- FAQ system
- Contact information and forms
- Help resources and documentation

### 7. Admin Portal

**Purpose**: Administration and configuration for SBF teams

- User & Company Configuration management
- Survey Configuration and customization
- Data Validation Workflow
- Analytics Dashboard for insights
- View/Edit Answer History
- Usage Logs and monitoring
- Role Definitions & Permissions
- CMS Management for content
- Adjust Scoring Logic capabilities

### 8. Reporting Engine

**Purpose**: Automates and standardises outputs

- Auto-generated Reports
- Recommendation Engine for insights
- Export Options (multiple formats)
- Integration with Power BI/Tableau/MS Teams

### 9. Collaboration Features

**Purpose**: Multi-user organizational support

- Single Company Login (Org-based authentication)
- Nominate Another User functionality
- Track Contributions across team members
- Access Rights at Survey Level granularity

### 10. Back-filing Capability

**Purpose**: Historical data integration

- Import past pilot survey data
- Data migration and validation
- Historical trend analysis support

## Technical Architecture Requirements

### Authentication & Authorization

- Role-based access control (RBAC)
- Organization-based user management
- Secure session management
- Multi-factor authentication support

### Data Management

- ACRA integration for company data auto-fill
- Secure data storage and encryption
- Data validation and integrity checks
- Audit trail for all data changes

### Performance & Scalability

- Responsive design for all devices
- Optimized loading times
- Scalable architecture for growing user base
- Caching strategies for improved performance

### Integration Requirements

- ACRA API integration
- Power BI/Tableau connectivity
- MS Teams integration
- PDF generation capabilities
- Email notification system

## Development Standards

### Code Organization

- Modular architecture following the defined modules
- Clear separation of concerns
- Reusable component library
- Consistent naming conventions

### Security Requirements

- Data encryption at rest and in transit
- Secure API endpoints
- Input validation and sanitization
- Regular security audits

### User Experience

- Intuitive navigation
- Progressive disclosure of information
- Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1)
- Mobile-first responsive design

## Success Metrics

- User engagement and completion rates
- Survey completion time optimization
- Report generation efficiency
- System uptime and reliability
- User satisfaction scores
